The paper proposes a new approach for few-shot classification, which is a problem commonly studied in the fields of machine learning and computer vision. The paper discusses the use of metric spaces and prototype representations, which are concepts commonly used in the sub-fields of machine learning and neural networks. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
